<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê SECTION 1: DATA CLASSIFICATION ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="divider-tag"><span class="num">SECTION 01</span></div>
  <p class="section-title">Classification of Data</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading">What Kind of Data Does Netflix Generate?</h2>
  <div class="data-types">
    <div class="data-card structured">
      <div class="tag">Structured</div>
      <div class="icon">üóÇÔ∏è</div>
      <h3>Structured Data</h3>
      <p>Neatly organised in rows & columns. Easily queried with SQL.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:12px; font-size:12px; color:#00C896; font-family:'Space Mono',monospace;">Examples at Netflix:</div>
      <p style="margin-top:4px; font-size:12px; color:#aaa;">‚Ä¢ User account details (name, plan, billing)<br>‚Ä¢ Watch history timestamps<br>‚Ä¢ Payment transaction records<br>‚Ä¢ Device login logs</p>
    </div>
    <div class="data-card semi">
      <div class="tag">Semi-Structured</div>
      <div class="icon">üìã</div>
      <h3>Semi-Structured Data</h3>
      <p>Has some organisational properties but doesn't fit rigid tables. Uses XML/JSON.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:12px; font-size:12px; color:#F5C518; font-family:'Space Mono',monospace;">Examples at Netflix:</div>
      <p style="margin-top:4px; font-size:12px; color:#aaa;">‚Ä¢ JSON API responses (search queries)<br>‚Ä¢ User preference metadata (tags, genres)<br>‚Ä¢ App event logs (click streams)<br>‚Ä¢ Device configuration files</p>
    </div>
    <div class="data-card unstructured">
      <div class="tag">Unstructured ‚Äî LARGEST VOLUME</div>
      <div class="icon">üé¨</div>
      <h3>Unstructured Data</h3>
      <p>No predefined format. The most complex and voluminous type ‚Äî impossible for traditional BI.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:12px; font-size:12px; color:#E50914; font-family:'Space Mono',monospace;">Examples at Netflix:</div>
      <p style="margin-top:4px; font-size:12px; color:#aaa;">‚Ä¢ Video content (thousands of hours uploaded)<br>‚Ä¢ Thumbnail images & artwork<br>‚Ä¢ Social media comments & reviews<br>‚Ä¢ Audio tracks & subtitles<br>‚Ä¢ Customer service chat transcripts</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê SECTION 2: 5 V's ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="divider-tag"><span class="num">SECTION 02</span></div>
  <p class="section-title">Characteristics of Big Data</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading">The 5 V's at Netflix</h2>
  <div class="five-vs">
    <div class="v-card">
      <div class="v-letter">V</div>
      <div class="v-name">Volume</div>
      <div class="v-desc">The sheer amount of data Netflix handles every single second</div>
      <div class="v-example">3.2 Petabytes logged daily. 1M+ hours of content watched every minute globally.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="v-card">
      <div class="v-letter">V</div>
      <div class="v-name">Velocity</div>
      <div class="v-desc">The speed at which data is generated, collected & processed</div>
      <div class="v-example">2 billion+ events tracked per hour. Real-time bitrate adjustments every 500ms per stream.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="v-card">
      <div class="v-letter">V</div>
      <div class="v-name">Variety</div>
      <div class="v-desc">The many different forms and formats of data</div>
      <div class="v-example">Video files, clickstream JSON, ratings (1‚Äì5), social text, images, payment CSVs ‚Äî all at once.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="v-card">
      <div class="v-letter">V</div>
      <div class="v-name">Veracity</div>
      <div class="v-desc">Accuracy & trustworthiness of the data collected</div>
      <div class="v-example">Bot views vs. real users. Incomplete profiles. Noisy clickstream data needs cleaning & validation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="v-card">
      <div class="v-letter">V</div>
      <div class="v-name">Value</div>
      <div class="v-desc">The business insights extracted from raw data</div>
      <div class="v-example">Recommendation engine drives 80% of all views. Saves Netflix ~$1 billion/year in churn prevention.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê SECTION 3: BI FAILS vs BIG DATA ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="divider-tag"><span class="num">SECTION 03 + 04</span></div>
  <p class="section-title">Why Traditional BI Fails & Why Big Data is Required</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading">Traditional BI vs. Big Data at Netflix</h2>

  <div class="vs-grid">
    <div class="vs-col">
      <div class="col-header bi">‚ùå Traditional BI ‚Äî Why It Fails</div>
      <div class="fail-card bad">
        <div class="label">Volume Problem</div>
        <h4>Cannot Scale to Petabytes</h4>
        <p>Relational databases like SQL Server or Oracle cannot handle Netflix's 3.2 PB/day. They crash or slow to hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fail-card bad">
        <div class="label">Velocity Problem</div>
        <h4>Batch Processing Only</h4>
        <p>Traditional BI runs reports overnight (ETL batch jobs). Netflix needs real-time recommendations ‚Äî not last night's data.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fail-card bad">
        <div class="label">Variety Problem</div>
        <h4>Structured Data Only</h4>
        <p>BI tools (Tableau, Power BI) need clean, tabular data. They cannot process video files, thumbnails, or social comments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fail-card bad">
        <div class="label">Architecture Problem</div>
        <h4>Single Server / Monolithic</h4>
        <p>Traditional BI scales vertically (bigger server). Netflix needs horizontal scaling across thousands of nodes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fail-card bad">
        <div class="label">Cost Problem</div>
        <h4>Prohibitively Expensive</h4>
        <p>Licensing enterprise BI tools (SAP, Oracle) at petabyte scale would cost hundreds of millions annually.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vs-center">
      <div class="vs-badge">VS</div>
    </div>

    <div class="vs-col">
      <div class="col-header bd">‚úÖ Big Data ‚Äî Why It's Required</div>
      <div class="bigdata-card">
        <div class="label">Solution: Scalable Storage</div>
        <h4>Hadoop HDFS + Amazon S3</h4>
        <p>Distributed file systems store petabytes cheaply across commodity hardware clusters. Scales linearly with demand.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bigdata-card">
        <div class="label">Solution: Real-Time Processing</div>
        <h4>Apache Kafka + Apache Spark</h4>
        <p>Kafka streams 2B+ events/hour. Spark processes them in milliseconds for instant recommendations and adaptive streaming.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bigdata-card">
        <div class="label">Solution: Multi-Format Support</div>
        <h4>Data Lake Architecture</h4>
        <p>Netflix's data lake on S3 stores all data types ‚Äî raw video, JSON logs, images, text ‚Äî processed by Spark & ML pipelines.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bigdata-card">
        <div class="label">Solution: Distributed Computing</div>
        <h4>Apache Spark + AWS EMR</h4>
        <p>Horizontally scalable clusters process data in parallel. Netflix uses thousands of EC2 nodes that scale up/down dynamically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bigdata-card">
        <div class="label">Solution: Open Source Stack</div>
        <h4>Hadoop Ecosystem (Free)</h4>
        <p>Netflix built its entire Big Data stack on open-source tools (Kafka, Spark, Presto, Druid), saving massive licensing costs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

