<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê WHY BIG DATA - SUMMARY ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="divider-tag"><span class="num">SUMMARY</span></div>
  <p class="section-title">Key Takeaways</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading">Why Netflix Cannot Exist Without Big Data</h2>
  <div class="why-grid">
    <div class="why-card" data-num="1">
      <div class="icon">üéØ</div>
      <h3>Hyper-Personalisation</h3>
      <p>Every user sees a different homepage. Big Data ML models analyse 100+ signals per user to rank 10,000+ titles in real-time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card" data-num="2">
      <div class="icon">üì°</div>
      <h3>Adaptive Streaming</h3>
      <p>Netflix changes video bitrate every 500ms based on your connection. This requires real-time stream processing ‚Äî impossible with BI batch jobs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card" data-num="3">
      <div class="icon">üí∞</div>
      <h3>Smarter Content Investment</h3>
      <p>Big Data analysis of viewing patterns, completion rates, and global trends tells Netflix which shows to greenlight ‚Äî reducing flops.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card" data-num="4">
      <div class="icon">üõ°Ô∏è</div>
      <h3>Fraud & Churn Prevention</h3>
      <p>Real-time anomaly detection flags suspicious logins. Churn prediction models proactively target at-risk subscribers with personalised offers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card" data-num="5">
      <div class="icon">üåç</div>
      <h3>Global Scale Operations</h3>
      <p>190+ countries, 238M+ users, peak hours at different times. Big Data infrastructure auto-scales globally ‚Äî traditional BI simply cannot.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card" data-num="6">
      <div class="icon">üñºÔ∏è</div>
      <h3>Dynamic Thumbnails</h3>
      <p>Netflix A/B tests 10‚Äì30 different thumbnails per title using Big Data feedback loops to show each user the artwork most likely to get a click.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

